      <levelledPara>
        <title>Theory of Operation</title>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Load Distribution</title>
          <para>
            The Center Body operates as a semi-monocoque structure, distributing flight 
            loads through the skin panels to longitudinal stringers and transverse frames. 
            This design provides optimal strength-to-weight ratio while maintaining structural 
            integrity under various flight conditions.
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
        
        <levelledPara>
          <title>Aerodynamic Integration</title>
          <para>
            The Center Body shape is optimized to blend seamlessly with the wing structure, 
            creating a continuous lifting surface. This integration reduces drag and improves 
            overall aerodynamic efficiency of the BWB configuration.
          </para>
        </levelledPara>
      </levelledPara>
    </description>
